---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Icon from '../components/Icon.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Where AI Fits"
  description="AI is a powerful accelerant — but it accelerates the motion you already have. If that motion has structural problems, AI makes them faster."
>
  <Nav />

  <!-- Page Hero -->
  <section class="bg-[#090e1a] pt-28 sm:pt-32 pb-16 sm:pb-20">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[1fr_260px] gap-12 lg:gap-16 items-end">
        <div>
          <p class="hero-eyebrow text-[11px] sm:text-[12px] font-medium text-white/30 uppercase tracking-[0.1em] mb-5">Where AI Fits</p>
          <h1 class="hero-headline text-[36px] sm:text-[48px] md:text-[60px] font-semibold tracking-[-0.03em] text-white leading-[1.05] max-w-3xl mb-6">
            AI accelerates.<br />
            <span class="text-white/35">It doesn't fix.</span>
          </h1>
          <p class="hero-sub text-[16px] sm:text-[18px] text-white/60 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
            AI tools are genuinely powerful for revenue teams. But they amplify the motion you already have —
            including its structural problems. Before you accelerate, you need to know what you're accelerating.
          </p>
        </div>
        <!-- Context callout -->
        <div class="hero-ctas flex flex-col gap-3 pb-2">
          <div class="card-ring-dark rounded-[10px] px-5 sm:px-6 py-5">
            <div class="text-[12px] sm:text-[13px] font-medium text-white/50 mb-3 uppercase tracking-[0.06em]">The sequence</div>
            <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
              {[
                { step: "Fix the structure", active: true, icon: "rebuild" },
                { step: "Instrument it", active: false, icon: "chart" },
                { step: "Accelerate with AI", active: false, icon: "trending-up" },
              ].map((item, i) => (
                <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                  <div class={`icon-ring-dark ${item.active ? 'opacity-100' : 'opacity-30'}`}>
                    <Icon name={item.icon} size={16} />
                  </div>
                  <span class={`text-[14px] ${item.active ? 'text-white font-medium' : 'text-white/35'}`}>{item.step}</span>
                </div>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Reality -->
  <section class="bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-16 sm:py-20">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 sm:gap-16 items-start">
        <div data-reveal>
          <h2 class="text-[26px] sm:text-[32px] font-semibold tracking-[-0.025em] text-[#171717] leading-[1.1] mb-6">
            The honest truth about AI in your revenue motion
          </h2>
          <p class="text-[15px] sm:text-[16px] text-[#4d4d4d] leading-relaxed mb-5">
            Every month there's a new AI tool promising to fix your pipeline, personalize your outreach,
            or automate your follow-up. Some of them are genuinely useful. Some are expensive distractions.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[15px] sm:text-[16px] text-[#4d4d4d] leading-relaxed mb-5">
            The problem isn't the tools. The problem is that AI gets layered on top of a broken motion.
            If your leads aren't converting because of a handoff problem, AI-personalized emails
            just get more of them to a broken handoff faster.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[15px] sm:text-[16px] text-[#4d4d4d] leading-relaxed">
            AI is an accelerant. The question is: what are you accelerating?
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card-ring rounded-[12px] p-6 sm:p-8 bg-white" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="120">
          <p class="text-[11px] sm:text-[12px] font-medium text-[#888888] uppercase tracking-[0.1em] mb-5">What AI can and can't do</p>
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-6">
            <div>
              <p class="text-[13px] font-semibold text-[#16a34a] mb-3">AI genuinely helps with</p>
              <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
                {[
                  "Scaling outreach and personalization",
                  "Summarizing calls and notes",
                  "Drafting proposals and follow-ups",
                  "Analyzing data and patterns",
                  "Onboarding content and training",
                ].map(i => (
                  <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <Icon name="check" size={14} />
                    <span class="text-[13px] sm:text-[14px] text-[#4d4d4d]">{i}</span>
                  </div>
                ))}
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="pt-5 border-t border-black/[0.06]">
              <p class="text-[13px] font-semibold text-[#dc2626] mb-3">AI can't fix</p>
              <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
                {[
                  "Broken handoffs between teams",
                  "Structural misalignment in your ICP",
                  "The wrong conversion architecture",
                  "Customers leaving for structural reasons",
                  "An expansion motion that doesn't exist",
                ].map(i => (
                  <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <Icon name="x" size={14} />
                    <span class="text-[13px] sm:text-[14px] text-[#4d4d4d]">{i}</span>
                  </div>
                ))}
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Right Order -->
  <section class="bg-[#fafafa] border-y border-black/[0.06]">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-16 sm:py-24">
      <div class="mb-10 sm:mb-12" data-reveal>
        <p class="text-[11px] sm:text-[12px] font-medium text-[#888888] uppercase tracking-[0.1em] mb-4">The Right Sequence</p>
        <h2 class="text-[28px] sm:text-[36px] md:text-[44px] font-semibold tracking-[-0.025em] text-[#171717] leading-[1.1] max-w-2xl">
          Structure first. AI second.
        </h2>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-5 sm:gap-6" data-reveal-group>
        {[
          {
            step: "First",
            title: "Fix the structure",
            body: "Close the structural leaks in your revenue journey. Get the motion working cleanly — right ICP, right handoffs, right conversion architecture, right expansion motion.",
            color: "#2563eb",
            icon: "rebuild"
          },
          {
            step: "Then",
            title: "Instrument it",
            body: "Build the metrics and feedback loops that let you see what's working. You need visibility into the motion before you automate it — otherwise you're flying blind at speed.",
            color: "#7c3aed",
            icon: "chart"
          },
          {
            step: "Now",
            title: "Accelerate with AI",
            body: "Layer AI tools on top of a clean, instrumented motion. Now you're accelerating something that works — personalization, scale, efficiency. That's when AI delivers real leverage.",
            color: "#059669",
            icon: "trending-up"
          },
        ].map(item => (
          <div class="card-ring rounded-[10px] p-6 sm:p-7 bg-white">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <div class="icon-ring" style={`background: ${item.color}12; color: ${item.color};`}>
                <Icon name={item.icon} size={18} />
              </div>
              <span class="text-[11px] font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.08em]" style={`color: ${item.color};`}>{item.step}</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-[18px] sm:text-[20px] font-semibold tracking-[-0.02em] text-[#171717] mb-3">{item.title}</h3>
            <p class="text-[13px] sm:text-[14px] text-[#4d4d4d] leading-relaxed">{item.body}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Where John fits -->
  <section class="bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-16 sm:py-20">
      <div class="max-w-3xl" data-reveal>
        <p class="text-[11px] sm:text-[12px] font-medium text-[#888888] uppercase tracking-[0.1em] mb-5">Where John Fits</p>
        <h2 class="text-[26px] sm:text-[32px] font-semibold tracking-[-0.025em] text-[#171717] leading-[1.1] mb-6">
          He helps you get the motion right before you accelerate it
        </h2>
        <p class="text-[15px] sm:text-[16px] text-[#4d4d4d] leading-relaxed mb-5">
          John works with companies that are about to invest in AI tools — or already have —
          and want to make sure the underlying revenue motion is clean before they scale it.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[15px] sm:text-[16px] text-[#4d4d4d] leading-relaxed mb-8">
          He also works with companies where AI adoption has accelerated a broken motion —
          and the problems are now bigger and moving faster. Structural diagnosis before you
          spend another dollar on tools that sit on top of the leak.
        </p>
        <a
          href="/book"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-5 sm:px-6 py-3 sm:py-3.5 bg-[#171717] text-white text-[14px] font-medium rounded-[6px] hover:bg-[#2a2a2a] transition-colors"
        >
          Talk about your AI strategy
          <Icon name="arrow-right" size={14} />
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
